[Data by country, area, or territory for 10 Mar 2022 can be accessed at https://promedmail.org/wp-content/uploads/world-pdf/2022%20WHO%20Data%20Tables%20MAR11_1647109366.pdf.

- The Americas region reported 9.1% of cases and 46.4% of deaths in the past 24 hours, having reported more than 148.63 million cases, 2nd to the European region as the most severely affected region. Brazil reported 54 906 cases, followed by the USA and Chile. An additional 7 countries reported more than 1000 cases (Peru, Canada, Argentina, Mexico, Guatemala, Costa Rica, and Uruguay) in the past 24 hours. Additionally, Cuba and Colombia reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The European region reported 46.2% of cases and 28.9% of deaths over the last 24 hours, as the most affected region, with cumulative cases exceeding 186.42 million. Some countries reporting few or no cases in the last 24 hours or longer include Belgium (15 cases), Switzerland (16 cases), and Tajikistan, among others. A total of 35 countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours -- 1 country reporting more than 100 000 cases, 12 reporting more than 10 000, 22 reporting over 1000 cases -- and no country reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The Eastern Mediterranean region reported 0.54% of daily case numbers and 2.2% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 21.38 million cases. Iran (6424) reported the highest number of cases over the last 24 hours. Pakistan and Iraq reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases over the last 24 hours. Tunisia, Egypt, Lebanon, Morocco, Kuwait, among others, did not report any cases over the last 24 hours.

- The African region reported 0.17% of daily cases and 0.47% of total deaths during the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 8.47 million cases. South Africa (1868) reported the highest number of cases over the last 24 hours, followed by Zimbabwe. A total of 23 countries did not report any cases over the last 24 hours. The low reported numbers are not a true reflection of the prevalent COVID-19 situation in the region.

- The Western Pacific region reported 41.1% of daily case numbers and 13.5% of deaths in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 30.74 million cases. South Korea (282 987) reported the highest number of cases over the last 24 hours, followed by Viet Nam, Japan, Australia, Malaysia, China, New Zealand, Singapore, Brunei, and Philippines.

- The South-East Asia region reported 2.7% of the daily newly reported cases and 8.2% of reported deaths in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 56.38 million cases. Thailand (24 792) reported the highest number of cases, followed by Indonesia (16 110), India (4194), Myanmar (956), Sri Lanka (467), Bhutan (389), and Bangladesh (267).

On the Overview tab at the WHO source URL, the epidemic curve of confirmed COVID-19 cases by WHO region, 30 Dec 2019 through 11 Mar 2022, is an excellent visual representation of the pandemic. - Mod.UBA]

